            "name": "Bernard Weinberger",
            "bio": "Rabbi Bernard \"Dov Zev\" Weinberger (d. 2018) was from the mid to late 20th century, rabbi of Young Israel of Williamsburg, Brooklyn. In the 1960s, he was the only Orthodox Jewish member of the New York City Council Against Poverty. In 1967, he was elected president of the Rabbinical Alliance. From 1972-1974, he was appointed to a special Human Resources Administrtaion post under NYC Mayor John V. Lindsay. He authored <em>Sefer Shem Tov al haTorah</em>.",
